The paper discusses the challenges and solutions for operationalizing machine learning-based security detections in a cloud environment, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of deploying these detections, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data silos, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
